observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management:
immediately create an Inventory Committee composed of an adequate number of members considering the quantity of the properties to be taken;
comply with the guidelines and procedures on inventory taking as provided in COA Circular 2020-006 and subsequently submit RPCPPE to the office of the Municipal Accountant;
direct the property custodian to prepare and maintain the necessary property cards; and
direct the Municipal Accountant to reconcile RPCPPE with their records and effect necessary adjusting entries when necessary and the copy which shall be furnished to the Office of the Auditor.

6.6.1 Direct the Project-in-Charge to submit to the Municipal Accountant a report showing the results of distribution of seedlings and fertilizers indicating specifically the names of the beneficiary-farmer, the number of seedlings and fertilizers given to each beneficiary-farmer and totality of the distributed stocks.
6.6.2 Direct the Project-in-Charge to obtain acknowledgment in the contract before a notary public for authenticity purposes and submit these as attachments to the report of distribution;
6.6.3 Direct the Municipal Accountant, upon receipt of the report, to record the distribution of the seedlings so that a more reliable figures of the affected accounts will be reflected in the financial statements.

We recommended that management direct the Municipal Accountant
to confirm with each of the claimants the amount of LGU’s liability;
to validate and verify the existence of the claims by coordinating the claimant and gathering the perfected contract or any document covering such liability;
effect necessary adjustments and furnish the Office of the Auditors with a copy of the journal entry voucher.

We recommended that Management:
establish responsibility center for GFPS under the Office of the Mayor;
direct the Municipal Accountant to provide RC code in the eNGAs;
direct the Municipal Budget Officer to provide RC code in the Budget.

17.9 We recommended that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) institutionalize the PSCP by creating a working group that will perform the following activities:
to conduct a risk assessment;
to identify critical processes and functions;
to determine scenarios that may disrupt regular operation;
to conduct risk analysis and impact analysis;
to formulate the PSCP based on the identified risks on critical processes and functions and its related steps to be followed; and
to submit a plan to the MDRRMO for review, to the LCE for approval, and to the Sangguniang Bayan for the passage of a resolution to institutionalize the PSCP.
17.10 We also recommended that Management improve their monitoring of operational requirements like the submission of PSCP.

We recommended that Management
immediately create an Inventory Committee composed of adequate number of members considering the quantity of the properties to be taken;
comply with the guidelines and procedures on inventory taking as provided in COA Circular 2020-006 and subsequently submit RPCPPE to the office of the Municipal Accountant;
direct the Inventory Committee to prepare and maintain the necessary property cards; and
direct the Municipal Accountant to reconcile RPCPPE with their records as well as effect necessary adjusting entries when necessary and the copy which shall be furnished to the Office of the Auditor.

We recommended that the management to:

Clearly indicate in the contract/job order the services/jobs of the personnel to be hired as well as their expected output;

Reevaluate the necessity and validity of hiring the job order and contractual personnel; 


Identify the nature of the duties and responsibilities of the  personnel in order to determine the proper account where their salaries/wages are to be accounted; and

Revisit the guidelines in hiring contractual and JO personnel as mentioned herein.

We recommended that management comply with the reporting guidelines of COA Circular No. 2015-008, as follows:

The Municipal Accountant shall record Road Network from the Registry of Public Infrastructure in the books as Property, Plant & Equipment;

The General Service Officer shall at the end of the accounting period render a Report on Local Road Network;

The total road network system shall be disclosed in the Notes to the Financial Statements; and

The Inventory Committee shall prepare the Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System.
